{"key":"processedPost-15492885","value":{"id":15492885,"first":15490249,"last":15493012,"when":1323488621,"utime":"12/10/11 05:43 AM","content":"Just to be clear, there's no reason to baby your cakes.&nbsp; I rinse them vigorously under the faucet after removing from the jars.&nbsp; You could even play a game of catch with them.&nbsp; They're pretty darned strong.<br /><br />After first flush, you'll get a better second flush if you'll allow the cakes to sit and slightly dry out for a week or so before soaking for the second flush.&nbsp; If you let them dry out like that, it's hard to put all that moisture back in with a mister, but a 12 to 24 hour soak does the trick.&nbsp; Mist to make up for evaporated moisture during the flushes.<br />RR","title":"Re: Spray bottle vs dunking","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}